DefectDescription: MAIN GEAR EXTENSION FAILURE
CarriedOutText:
1. ALL ELECTRICAL CONNECTORS REMOVED AND CLEANED. LANDING GEAR TIME DELAY PCB A316 REMOVED AND CLEANED. 5 X RETRACTIONS CARRIED OUT AND FOUND SERVICEABLE.
2. THE CREW REPORTED THAT THE LANDING GEAR FAILED TO EXTENDED WHEN SELECTED. IT EXTENDED DURING ANOTHER ATTEMPT AND THEY GOT 3 GREENS.
3. THE AIRCRAFT LANDED SAFELY IN KABUL AND WAS TOWED TO THE PACTEC HANGER TO CARRY OUT TROUBLESHOOTING, RETRACTIONS AND EXTENSIONS.
4. THE AIRCRAFT WAS PLACED ON JACKS AS PER MM129-590000-15 REV C1 CAHPTER 07-10-00-2 PAR 1A.
5. LEAK CHECK WAS CARRIED OUT AS PER MM129-590000-15 REV C1 CHAPTER 32-30-00-1 PAR 1A AND NO LEAKS EVIDENT.
6. LANDING GEAR TIME DELAY PRINTED CIRCUIT BOARD WAS CHECKED AS PER AMM129-59000-15 CHAPTER 32-30-0-1 REV C1 PAR 2A 1-11, NIL DEFECTS NOTED, THE PCB WAS CLEANED AND RE-INSTALLED.
7. CHAPTER 32-30-00-1 PAS 3A WAS NOT CONSIDERED TO BE DONE AS PER TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE BECAUSE THE AIRCRAFT DIDN'T EXPERIENCE A GEAR UP PROBLEM, BUT A GEAR EXTENSION PROBLEM,
8. ALSO REF TO MM129-59000-15 REV C1 CHAPTER 32-30-00-1, PAGE 5 ITEM 4G, THE LANDING GEAR DELAY CIRCUIT BREAKER CHECKED FOR SERVICEABILITY AND FOUND SERVICEABLE.
9. ALL ELECTRICAL CONNECTORS WERE CHECKED FOR SECURITY OF ATTACHMENT AND FOUND SERVICEABLE.
10. IN TOTAL 5 RETRACTIONS AND EXTENSIONS WERE CARRIED OUT AND WE HAD 3 GREENS WITH EVERY CYCLE AND THE AIRCRAFT WAS FOUND TO BE SERVICEABLE.
11. THE AIRCRAFT WAS LOWERED AS PER AMM CHAPTER 07-10-00-2 PAR 1B AND RETURNED TO SERVICE.
